epiphany-webkit (2.27.1-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * New upstream release.
  * debian/copyright:
  - updated, with information on the help files, which are FDL, but are OK
    to distribute, given the outcome of our last vote
  * debian/control.in:
  - build-dep on libsoup-gnome2.4-dev
  - make epiphany-webkit-dev depend on libwebkit-dev
  * debian/patches/13_gtk-doc_fix.patch:
  - removed; applied upstream
  * debian/patches/99_*:
  - refreshed
  * 02_ac_init.patch:
  - adapted for epiphany-webkit
  * 04_move_tabs.patch, 06_ssl_weak_ciphers.patch, 11_useragent-weasel.patch,
    13_extensions_need_xpcom.patch, 21_chrome_certmanager.patch,
    30_ua_debian_version.patch:
  - dropped; gecko-only, does not apply to trunk
  * 05_libexecdir.patch, debian/rules:
  - removed gecko-specific parts of the patch
  * 09_download_dialog.patch:
  - refreshed, with gecko-only part removed; notice that this patch is not
    currently useful since Epiphany and WebKitGTK+ do not support
    downloading, and will need a revision after such functionality lands
  * 10_smart_bookmarks.patch, 99_autoreconf.patch: refreshed
  * 13_gtk-doc_fix.patch:
  - added; do not try to include ephy-cookie-manager in the documentation,
    since it no longer exists
  * 14_webkit_temporary_gconf_rename.patch:
  - patch to rename all gconf keys used by epiphany, to allow sane
    parallel installation with the gecko version
  * 15_webkit_temporary_gettext_domain_rename.patch:
  - patch to make epiphany look for translations in epiphany-webkit.mo
    files instead of epiphany.mo
  * debian/epiphany-webkit-data.gconf-defaults, debian/rules: updated
    accordingly
  * debian/epiphany-webkit.{preinst,postrm},
    debian/epiphany-webkit-data.{preinst,postrm}:
  - add diversions for files we have in common with epiphany-gecko and are
    shareable

 -- Gustavo Noronha Silva <kov@debian.org>  Wed, 29 Apr 2009 10:49:56 -0300

epiphany-browser (2.24.3-2) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Fix .pc file by hand so that extensions build correctly.
  * 10_smart_bookmarks.patch: fix crash introduced by the patch because 
    the text is not checked for NULLity. Closes: #516286.

 -- Josselin Mouette <joss@debian.org>  Tue, 17 Feb 2009 18:29:06 +0100

epiphany-browser (2.24.3-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * Move the contents of README.Debian to epiphany-browser.README.Debian 
    so that it is actually shipped.
  * epiphany-browser-data.gconf-defaults: enable the universal encoding 
    detector, to improve display of broken sites.
  * New upstream release.
  * 00_browser_wrapper_path.patch, 01_bookmarks_menu.patch, 
    03_dbus.patch, 07_bookmarks.patch: refreshed.
  * 99_autoreconf.patch: updated for the new version.
  * 10_smart_bookmarks.patch: new patch to fix the smart bookmarks 
    behavior. Always use the text from the entry to initiate a search, 
    and fill it automatically when using middle-click.
  * Drop epiphany-webkit build for now as it has gone away from the 2.24 
    branch. Don’t worry, it will be soon back for good in experimental.
  * 30_ua_debian_version.patch: new patch to add the Debian version to 
    the user agent string. Closes: #509207.
  * rules: pass the appropriate macro so that it works.

 -- Josselin Mouette <joss@debian.org>  Sun, 15 Feb 2009 01:37:24 +0100

